   There was a significant difference in dissocial behavior cases between male and female adolescents (chi(2) [1, N=194]=14.75, p<.00), with Yates' correction: (chi(2) [1, N=194]=12.59, p<.01). The percentage of cases is 18% in women and 45% in men.
